    "narrative": "The spotlight today shines brightest on **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, who carries the slate\u2019s highest efficiency score (78.36). While his matchup against McCullers Jr. is theoretically favorable, the real value here is the optimization of his stolen base potential; the combination of a slow opposing delivery and the 5x5 scarcity factor makes **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** an automatic start. Similarly, **Trevor Story** (75.93) is our strongest leverage play, benefiting from a +16% park adjustment that helps mitigate a neutral platoon stance. **James Wood** also earns a \"Strong\" designation (73.18) as his leadoff spot against the left-handed Hudson, B provides optimal opportunities for run production, balancing the risk of a sub-elite opposing pitcher.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Seiya Suzuki**, who landed just outside our active threshold with a 44.16 score. While **Seiya Suzuki** offers reliable base utility, the optimizer correctly prioritized the dynamic platoon and speed-based upside of **Mickey Moniak** (64.12), whose profile is significantly enhanced by his matchup against Peralta, F. We are exercising caution with **Brice Turang** (49.29) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (47.90) today; while both occupy active slots, they are hitting against elite-tier pitching (Skenes and Eovaldi, respectively), which suppresses their ceiling and moves them dangerously close to our \"Below Floor\" category. \n\nWe must remain alert to the situational risks attached to the lower half of our lineup. **Jose Caballero** (56.31) and **Alex Freeland** (47.84) are both relegated to the bottom of the order, which acts as a heavy anchor on their efficiency scores. **Jose Caballero** in particular is facing a sharp negative platoon adjustment, and though he has the speed to capitalize on the McCullers Jr. delivery, the lack of lineup support makes his output volatile. We are comfortable keeping **Max Muncy** (39.73) and **Kyle Karros** (40.89) on the bench to preserve our game caps, as neither offered a statistical profile strong enough to overcome the high probability of limited return against tough opposing starters.",
